<figureCitation box="[370,407,1027,1053]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[188,231,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Megatrigon spp., left antenna, lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. (♁). G. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). M. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849886/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">3C</figureCitation>
). Microtrichiose stripes on face along eye margin wide and long, extended till tentorial pit and joined with microtrichia below antenna by oblique microtrichiose stripe; distance between eyes a little larger than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[436,591,1098,1123]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[436,591,1098,1123]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">M. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[598,731,1097,1124]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 0.17 × width of head; ocellar triangle isosceles, without median longitudinal groove; colour of postpedicel (
<figureCitation box="[792,882,1133,1159]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[188,231,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Megatrigon spp., left antenna, lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. (♁). G. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). M. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849886/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
) dictinctly darker than pedicel.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[189,1398,1198,1295]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">THORAX. Mesoscutum with two, wide, lateral microtrichiose stripes and two weak submedian microtrichiose stripes starting as triangular markings and ending as small spots at the level of transverse suture; supra-alar setae yellow; median about 0.50 of width of mediotergite covered by microtrichia.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[189,1398,1334,1396]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">WING. Membrane not infuscated, with yellow veins and microtrichia; cell br above vena spuria completely covered with microtrichia; costagium with yellow setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[189,1399,1434,1567]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
LEGS. Dark submedian ring on pro- and mesotibia weak and visible only ventrally, microtrichia on metatibia distinct in proximal half, dorsally; all tarsi yellow-orange, without shading; all setae of legs light yellow; tarsomere 1 of pro- and metaleg not swollen like in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[954,1109,1506,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[954,1109,1506,1531]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">M. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1116,1249,1505,1531]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; tarsomere 1 of protarsus anterodorsally without a line of minute black spinules between the yellow trichia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[189,1399,1606,1808]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
ABDOMEN (
<figureCitation box="[318,392,1606,1632]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[241,1346,265,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[241,1346,265,1784]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Megatrigon spp., habitus, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. (♁). G. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). M. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849878" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849878/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[407,445,1606,1632]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1862,1888]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,265,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1399,265,1837]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Megatrigon spp., abdomen, dorsal view, ♁. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849902/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">7C</figureCitation>
). Tergites light yellow setose; tergites 2+3 with very large silver spots, covering most of the tergite’s width except for a narrow brown goblet–shaped median part; distance between silver spots on tergite 2 smaller, 0.19 × width of tergite; spots on tergite 3 not tapering towards the middle of tergite, but being more rounded; silver spots on tergites 2+3 covered with relatively long, dense, adpressed, yellow setae except antero-lateral corner; tergite 4 with two small indistinct microtrichiose spots near to anterior margin. Male genitalia in 
<figureCitation box="[746,856,1782,1808]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,232,1825,1851]" captionTargetBox="[216,1374,263,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[216,1374,263,1796]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 10. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, epandrium, left lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. Megatrigon sp. from sexfasciatus group. M. M. nivalis. Symbols: x = ventral margin of median surstyle; y = posterior surstyle; z = cercus; w = subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849914" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849914/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Figs 10C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[868,918,1782,1808]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1758,1784]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,340,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[189,1399,340,1716]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 11. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, hypandrium (A–M) and phallus (N), left lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. M. sp. from sexfasciatus group. M–N. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. Symbol: x = hamus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849918" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849918/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">11C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[930,983,1782,1808]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[189,232,1794,1820]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,442,1753]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[189,1399,442,1753]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 12. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, hypandrium, ventral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. apiformis sp. nov. G. M. cooksoni sp. nov. H. M. immaculatus sp. nov. I. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. J. M. tabanoides sp. nov. K. Megatrigon sp. from the sexfasciatus group. L. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. Symbol: x = lateral ‘shoulders’." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849922" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849922/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">12C</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
